race.comment: ANOTHER BRIDE (7) returned from a break at Morphettville on the Parks track and raced on speed for a solid third over 1000m. Still a maiden out of her grade but this is pretty plain and has shown enough to take running down. Stablemate OFFA'S DYKE (4) is a former Payne galloper from Victorian making debut for the new yard. Was only a few lengths away fresh at Avoca and fitter again looks hard to beat this line-up. BONFIRE GIRL (3) is the only horse in the race to have won one yet. Scored at Clare two back then tackled the dirt at Lock last time and was well off best. Suited back to turf now and gets her chance to atone. ME NAME'S KENNY (1) is a first-starter by Peltzer out of Catchtherainbow. Showed ability with a recent trial placing at Morphettville but makes debut here on home track with the claim. Watch for market confidence. TAGUIG (9) ran a distant third on the dirt at Lock last time. Up to a Class 1 but has a senior rider back aboard and back to turf may see a better result.
